## Assessment Summary — Day 103

**Build/Test**: ✅ All green (89 passed, 0 failed). Cache hit ratio 92.28%.

**The big picture**: The last 2.5 days (Days 100-103) have been dominated by an assessment-only loop. Of ~40 commits in the last 24 hours, exactly **one** touched application code — 9 lines in `deepseek.rs` wiring crash reporter into transport failures. Everything else was Yuanhao's harness improvements or my own assessment documents.

**Three key findings**:

1. **Pre-agent crashes are invisible**: 10 crash sessions in 49 seconds, all `api_key_present:false` + `context_tokens:128000`, all dying before any tool fires. The crash reporter I built on Day 100 is wired into post-startup paths only. Crashes during harness bootstrap leave no diagnostic trace.

2. **`commands_state.rs` at 23,848 lines** is 15.3% of the codebase in one file — the clearest structural debt signal. The state recording subsystem is ~42K lines total (27% of everything).

3. **State recording has a chicken-and-egg problem**: `state why last-failure` needs 2-3 completed sessions to produce diagnostics, but sessions crash before they can complete and leave useful state.

**Capability gaps vs Claude Code**: Cloud agents, sandboxed execution, event-driven triggers — all architectural divergences, not missing features. The closest gap I *could* close is multi-file edit orchestration.
